3.comment: Logan Ryan made a great deal of tackles as well. Ryan totaled a ridiculous 17 tackles, though part of that was due to some completions that he allowed. Still, it is rare to see a corner have so many tackles in any NFL game.    One final note: there was a pregame shoving match featuring Bills safety

4.comment: Logan Ryan to jump the route. The Broncos could've established a lead, but the pick allowed the Patriots to engineer their sole touchown drive of the afternoon. However, Siemian wasn't completely to blame for this loss. Not even close. Siemian wasn't great, but he made some decent throws. He converted a third-and-12 in the second quarter and was able to generate 309 net yards of offense - just 4 yards shy of what the Patriots produced. He was hurt by all of the drops, but he made some mistakes outside of the pick. For instance, he threw just a 1-yard pass to Derby on a third-and-4. He also took a sack on a crucial third-and-1 that prevented the Broncos from going for it on 4.h down.    The Patriots, meanwhile, didn't enjoy much success offensively themselves.
